1. make sure the repository is cloned locally, and make sure git is directed to the correct path (for example: "c:/users/pinda/testGit")

2. git status to check if all is good

3. use notepad or visual studio or whatever to make changes to file

4. git add "file name" or add . to add changes to a new commit

5. git commit -m "new commit message"

6. git push

done